layers will not be subject too.   In some of the player information, you see there is a limit set on the number of players that can play this class.   I am tentatively planning on allowing as many as 4 Paladins but that is assuming we have between 60-80 full time players.  If for technical reasons, we have fewer players then I will reduce the number of allowable Paladin players.    You will not be able to split class to the Paladin period.<br><br>The Paladin will be subject to certain game aspects that will require them to police themselves because I do not think the game system will be able to do the task.  Paladins will begin the game in the role of a squire who will have very limited abilities, the player will be unable to access some of the Paladin’s normal abilities such as Lay of Hands.  Only after the player has completed the quests required to be accepted into the order of Paladins will he have full access to those Paladin abilities.   Since the game system does not have the functionality to allow me to turn off/on individual class abilities, the player will be responsible for limiting himself to those abilities that are allowed based on his current role in the plot.<br><br>A second issue the Paladin player must keep in mind is the fact that his character may not be available to him at all times.   Without giving away too much of the storyline, certain events may unfold (largely dependent on actions taken by the player base) that may place the Paladin in an unplayable status.   Any player choosing to play a Paladin class should keep this in mind and have a secondary character that he/she can play during these periods in the story line.<br><br>Third, as it has been stated that the Paladin class is one of the prime motivators within the storyline, it is extremely important that those specific players be ones that consistently play.   If a player does not have the time to commit to playing this class, then I strongly recommend playing a different class.  If a person chooses to play the Paladin class but fails to consistently play, I will very likely terminate the character and adjust the storyline appropriately to account for a new paladin player.<br><br>Obviously, there are many disadvantages to playing the paladin class and making the choice to play the class should be undertaken only after carefully reviewing the above information.   These limitations are placed on that specific class with no commitment from myself that the Paladin would in turn receive rewards that commensurate those critical disadvantages.   <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub26.ezboard.com/fapex71990frm23.showPrevMessage?topicID=4.topic"> <img src="http://www.nutrocker.co.uk/board/blPrevTopic12.gif" border=0></a><a href="http://pub26.ezboard.com/fapex71990frm23.showNextMessage?topicID=4.topic"> <img src="http://www.nutrocker.co.uk/board/blNextTopic12.gif" border=0> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub26.ezboard.com/fapex71990frm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic><img src=http://www.nutrocker.co.uk/board/blAddReply12.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub26.ezboard.com/fapex71990frm23.emailToFriend?topicID=4.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub26.ezboard.com/fapex71990frm23.threadControl?topicID=4.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub26.ezboard.com/fapex71990frm23.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub26.ezboard.com/fapex71990frm23.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?top